### Description

Commit https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/commit/c3a15cb3 introduced a duplication of a small code block in the `HttpClientBuilder`:

```java
            if (!reuseConnections) {
                builder.setConnectionReuseStrategy(new NoConnectionReuseStrategy());
            }
```

The duplicate code block should be removed.

### Before reporting an issue

- [x] I have read and understood the above terms for submitting issues, and I understand that my issue may be closed without action if I do not follow them.

### Area

admin/ui

### Describe the bug

We are trying to upgrade from 16.1 to 25+ and see failure when using a custom `ClientAuthenticatorFactory` extension that uses `configProperties`. With 25 and 26 the fields didn't show up at all (see https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/33729)

Now with 26.1 they do show up but saving gives the error: **Client could not be updated: Invalid json representation for ClientRepresentation. Unrecognized field "`config`" at line 1 column 3612.**

### Version

26.1

### Regression

- [x] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

I expect that when having custom properties the client should allow to save.
I also expected that we can use **`getConfigProperties`** or **`getConfigPropertiesPerClient`** but it seems PerClient is never called. API states: _Applicable only if "`isConfigurablePerClient`" is true_ but this seems non-existent

### Actual behavior

Fields are visible with 26.1 but when trying to save you get an error. **Client could not be updated: Invalid json representation for `ClientRepresentation`. Unrecognized field "config" at line 1 column 3612.**

### How to Reproduce?

Create a custom extension that implements `ClientAuthenticator`, `ClientAuthenticatorFactory` and returns a list of Properties

```
private static final List<ProviderConfigProperty> configProperties = new ArrayList<>();
    static {
        ProviderConfigProperty exceptionsList = new ProviderConfigProperty();
        exceptionsList.setType(ProviderConfigProperty.STRING_TYPE);
        exceptionsList.setName(CONDITION_EXCEPTIONS_LIST);
        exceptionsList.setLabel("Exceptions");
        exceptionsList.setHelpText("The list of exceptions in CIDR or IP-range format.\nIf client's IP address will match any of these ranges, use ## to seperate due to bug with lists in this context");
        configProperties.add(exceptionsList);

        ProviderConfigProperty debugAllowed = new ProviderConfigProperty();
        debugAllowed.setType(ProviderConfigProperty.BOOLEAN_TYPE);
        debugAllowed.setName(CONDITION_DEBUG_ALLOW);
        debugAllowed.setLabel("Debug");
        debugAllowed.setHelpText("If turned ON, some debug data will be written in the log file");
        configProperties.add(debugAllowed);
    }
    @Override
    public List<ProviderConfigProperty> getConfigProperties() {
        return configProperties;
    }
    @Override
    public List<ProviderConfigProperty> getConfigPropertiesPerClient() {
        return configProperties;
    }
```

### Anything else?
Sample maven project
[keycloak-client-iprange.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/18437455/keycloak-client-iprange.zip)

I tested 24, 25, 26 and 26.1 they all seem broken, this probably explains why there are not many fresh extensions using this around.
_No response_
